                <p>August 2, 1891, illegally seized 20 miles southeast by east off Copper Island, by
                    the Russian man-of-war <hi rend="italic">Aleut</hi>, the commander said, for
                    being in Russian waters, for which I protested, as I was in neutral waters and
                    on the high seas for all nations.</p>
